  "texts": [
    "These observations suggest improved crystallinity and stronger bonding in the lattice.",
    "Such enhancements are likely due to optimized stoichiometry, which leads to a more cohesive crystal structure.In samples prepared with 40% excess Bismuth (70: 30), distinct behavioural differences emerge compared to compositions with a lower bismuth content.",
    "Raman spectroscopy reveals significant alterations in the vibrational properties of these materials.",
    "Specifically, the A 1 -2 and A 1 -3 modes exhibit noticeable blue shifts, indicative of increased vibrational frequencies that may arise from strengthened lattice bonds or local compression [43].",
    "Concurrently, these peaks show pronounced broadening and marked reduction in intensity (Figure 6(d))."
